24009 offered by President Baer's resolution to request Board of Health implement winter eviction moratorium.

948
01:13:57,029 --> 01:14:10,875
Whereas many cities and countries prohibited evictions between November 1 and March 31 due to winter cold that puts lives in danger and whereas Massachusetts has yet to implement a statewide policy to protect families from becoming unhoused

949
01:14:11,400 --> 01:14:21,226
and put out on the street in dangerously cold weather, and whereas over 1,200 households were evicted in Massachusetts in the winter of 2022 through 2023.

950
01:14:21,926 --> 01:14:36,775
Now, therefore, be it resolved by the Medford City Council that we request that the Board of Health declare an annual state of emergency and implement an eviction moratorium each winter to protect the health and safety of residents who face potentially fatal illness if evicted during the winter.

951
01:14:37,515 --> 01:14:37,975
President Behrs.

952
01:14:38,496 --> 01:14:40,037
Thank you, President Collins.

953
01:14:42,085 --> 01:15:06,594
essentially the purpose of this resolution is, as you just read, there have been calls from residents that I've heard from here in Medford, organizations statewide like Greater Boston Legal Services, requesting that communities look into, especially their boards of health, adopting this kind of state of emergency for the winter months to prevent evictions just for the cold weather.

954
01:15:06,614 --> 01:15:08,895
It certainly would not stop the

955
01:15:09,855 --> 01:15:11,436
legal process from going forward.

956
01:15:13,077 --> 01:15:17,521
And quite frankly, you'd probably have a big cliff effect where on April 1st, you'd see quite many evictions.

957
01:15:17,601 --> 01:15:37,615
And I think that's something we need to consider as well, but especially addressing the issue of putting people out in the street in the cold, in the dangerously cold winter weather with the shelter system for the state at maximum capacity with the lack of capacity or, you know, 24 hour shelters here in Medford.

958
01:15:39,676 --> 01:15:42,677
this resolution is the folks who can implement this is the Board of Health.

959
01:15:42,797 --> 01:15:43,698
We can't implement it.

960
01:15:44,138 --> 01:15:45,479
I don't even think the mayor can implement it.

961
01:15:45,499 --> 01:15:48,940
It would be the Board of Health under some state regulations.

962
01:15:49,720 --> 01:15:52,462
And Greater Boston Legal Services does have more information on that.

963
01:15:53,322 --> 01:15:59,905
But I did want to put this on the agenda and send this over to the Board of Health to request that they consider

964
01:16:00,649 --> 01:16:04,392
taking this action to protect the health and safety of Medford residents.

965
01:16:05,132 --> 01:16:08,875
So I would move to refer this to the Board of Health for their consideration.

966
01:16:09,435 --> 01:16:12,178
Thank you for your consideration, my fellow colleagues.

967
01:16:14,920 --> 01:16:18,582
Councillor Lazaro.

968
01:16:18,602 --> 01:16:21,745
I appreciate you putting this on the agenda, President Behrs.

969
01:16:24,269 --> 01:16:30,354
One of my jobs right now, I'm the assistant director of the Malden Warming Center, which is a seasonal shelter in Malden.

970
01:16:30,434 --> 01:16:33,817
It's an overnight shelter for people who are unhoused.

971
01:16:34,238 --> 01:16:38,982
And we are open from December 1 through March 30th yearly.

972
01:16:39,262 --> 01:16:44,006
And I can also say that in November, we get a lot of people calling us saying, are you open yet?

973
01:16:44,106 --> 01:16:45,607
Because it's cold in November too.

974
01:16:47,909 --> 01:16:51,973
We should be doing anything and everything that we can to make sure that people can stay in their homes

975
01:16:52,557 --> 01:16:58,922
when it's cold out, it doesn't even have to be below freezing for people to face a lot of health issues from exposure.

976
01:17:00,423 --> 01:17:13,232
We had a guest recently with, we're not a medical facility, we are run by volunteers and just people just with no training in any kind of medical things at the center that I work at.

977
01:17:14,887 --> 01:17:19,729
So when we have folks that have real medical issues, we frequently have to call ambulances.

978
01:17:19,829 --> 01:17:30,533
And we have a guest who has COPD, and he, just because of exposure from being outside, goes to the hospital really frequently, has a lot of breathing problems just from being outside during the day, even on days when it's not that cold.

979
01:17:30,593 --> 01:17:32,293
So it really is very dangerous for people.

980
01:17:32,333 --> 01:17:41,597
And if there is anything that we can do as a council, just small steps towards mitigating that for our residents, I think we should make sure that we're taking those steps.

981
01:17:42,182 --> 01:17:43,624
I appreciate you putting it on the agenda.

982
01:17:43,704 --> 01:17:48,552
